caption: A great Indian restaurant. Not glamorous, not glitzy, no meat. Just extremely good vegetarian food, the friendliest service, and unbelievably, unbeatably cheap prices. When you walk in you feel like you've stepped into a shop on another continent. There are old guys hanging out making jokes.  You can't tell who works there. The menu is way out of date. You go up to the counter and order way too much food -- an absurd amount -- having no idea how much it should cost. The waiter thinks for a second and then charges you $8.70. Whatever you get, it's delicious. Make sure you get some samosas and chai on the side.  Shelve the photogenic $20 masala joint. Support your local cheap-as-hell Indian restaurant. Your wallet and your stomach will thank you.
